race.comment: GOD'S GRIN (7) is knocking on the door of a maiden win, finishing 2.1L off the winner last start when the race favourite at Bunbury. This looks an easier race on paper and the stable have booked the stable strike jockey. Maps to be prominent from the draw and can shed the maiden tag. SHE'SATROOPER (10) hasn't been far away recently, missing by 2L at this track and trip most recently. Derrick knows her well and she looks set to put her best foot forward. LATORIO (9) just missed at Northam two back through a good form race before a 1.6L defeat last start at York. She's better than she showed there and while she's likely to get back from the draw, a return to her best form will see her hard to hold out. BLACK CILLA (11) will need some luck from the draw but can feature if she's up to the mark. CLASSIC TURN (12) can improve dropping in trip.
